  "research_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">Fragments on Virtue and Fate is a modern scholarly compilation of fifty-nine fragmentary passages of elegiac poetry, unified by their thematic focus on the concepts of human excellence and cosmic destiny. The verses are not derived from a single, continuous poem but are excerpts preserved through quotation in later prose authors, most notably the Stoic philosopher Chrysippus and the anthologist Stobaeus. As a collection of gnomic poetry, it employs the elegiac couplet to deliver concise, authoritative statements on ethics and the nature of the cosmos. The content addresses the core preoccupations of early Greek wisdom literature, exploring the supreme value of virtue, the fixed and divine order of fate, and the complex relationship between divine justice, human agency, and predetermined outcomes.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">The work survives exclusively through this secondary transmission, having been cited by Chrysippus to provide poetic support for Stoic philosophical doctrines and later anthologized by Stobaeus. This mode of preservation ensured its survival within the stream of philosophical discourse rather than as an independent literary text. The fragments hold historical significance primarily for their demonstrable influence on Hellenistic philosophy, particularly Stoicism, which adopted them as venerable poetic antecedents for its own teachings. Today, they are studied both as valuable examples of pre-philosophical Greek ethical thought and for their critical role in understanding the Stoic reception and reinterpretation of earlier poetic tradition.</p>\n</div>",
  "rows": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "1",
      "text": "παῖδες Ἀρίστωνος, κλεινοῦ θεῖον γένος ἀνδρός.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "2",
      "text": "αὐτὰρ ἀνὴρ ἀγαθὸς τοτὲ μὲν κακός, ἄλλοτε δ’ ἐσθλός.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "3",
      "text": "ἐσθλοὶ μὲν γὰρ ἁπλῶς, παντοδαπῶς δὲ κακοί.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "4",
      "text": "πολλὰς δὴ φιλίας ἀπροσηγορία διέλυσεν.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "5",
      "text": "οὐκέτι γιγνώσκουσιν Ἀθηναῖοι Μεγαρῆας.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "6",
      "text": "ἔγχει καὶ Κήδωνι διάκονε, μηδ’ ἐπιλήθου, εἰ χρὴ τοῖς ἀγαθοῖς ἀνδράσιν οἰνοχοεῖν.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "7",
      "text": "Λὶψ ἄνεμος ταχὺ μὲν νεφέλας, ταχὺ δ’ αἴθρια ποιεῖ· Ἀργέστηι δ’ ἀνέμωι πᾶς’ ἕπεται νεφέλη. ⊗",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "8",
      "text": "οὔ μοι ἔτ’ εὐκελάδων ὕμνων μέλει οὐδ’ ἔτι μολπῆς,",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "10",
      "text": "ἐσθλὸς ἐὼν ἄλλου κρείττονος ἀντέτυχεν·",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "11",
      "text": "κοῦραι ἐλαφρὰ ποδῶν ἴχνι’ ἀειράμεναι.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "12",
      "text": "ἐν δὲ διχοστασίηι καὶ ὁ πάγκακος ἔλλαχε τιμῆς.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "14",
      "text": "τοιάδε ( ) θνητοῖσι †κακὰ κακῶν† ἀμφί τε Κῆρες εἰλεῦνται, κενεὴ δ’ ἔκδυσις οὐδ’ ἀθέρι—;",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "15",
      "text": "†ἦν θεός· ἢ κρέσσων δέ τι ὀνησόμεθα.†",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "16",
      "text": "ὀλίγης ἐστὶ διδασκαλίας,",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "17",
      "text": "ἔς τε μέσον πεδίον Στενυκλήριον ἔς τ’ ὄρος ἄκρον εἵπετ’ Ἀριστομένης τοῖς Λακεδαιμονίοις.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "19",
      "text": "ἀνδρὶ μὲν αὐλητῆρι θεοὶ νόον οὐκ ἐνέφυσαν, ἀλλ’ ἅμα τῶι φυσῆν χὠ νόος ἐκπέταται.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "20",
      "text": "ἡμεῖς δ’ εἰς Ἕλλης πόντον ἀπεπλέομεν.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "21",
      "text": "Ζεὺς πάντων αὐτὸς φάρμακα μοῦνος ἔχει.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "22",
      "text": "οὐκ ἔστιν μείζων βάσανος χρόνου οὐδενὸς ἔργου, ὃς καὶ ὑπὸ στέρνοις ἀνδρὸς ἔδειξε νόον.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "23",
      "text": "ὤφελεν ὡς ἀφανὴς οὕτω φανερώτατος εἶναι καιρός· ὃς αὐξάνεται πλεῖστον ἀπ’ εὐλαβίης.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "24",
      "text": "†τόλμ’ ἀεὶ κἄν τι τρηχὺ νέμωσι θεοί.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "25",
      "text": "ἡ νεότης ἀσύφηλος ἀεὶ θνητοῖσι τέτυκται· εἰ δὲ δίκην βλάπτοι, πουλὺ χερειοτέρη.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "26",
      "text": "τὸν φρουρὸν φρουρεῖν χρή, τὸν ἐρῶντα δ’ ἐρᾶν.",
      "witness_prefix": "",
      "speaker": null
    },
